e the info.  <br>
<br>
I am 100% positive it works, because if it didn't, I would have had one gurl in tears after the amount of time she and I lived in PoF for the Golem....<br>
<br>
#1.  All the crap to get to the point where the gnome would give you the gear, there are MANY ways to avoid.  <br>
    a. Shaman who are + truspirit can ask for the gear.<br>
    b. Chanters through use of Faction mod spells can ask for the gear.<br>
    c. Bards with faction adjustment song can ask for the gear.<br>
    d. You can spend tons of money and time to get the faction up, which is just silly.<br>
<br>
#2. Got gear, give to golem, kill golem, Wizzie loots the  oil. <br>
<br>
#3 Wizzie makes trip back to Gnome.  Gnome gives wizzie the bird. DO NOT HAND IN THE ITEM.<br>
Put the item in the trade window, have someone invis you while you stand there, with the trade window open. Check that con is now &quot;indifferent&quot; Hit trade.  You will get the staff.<br>
<br>
#4.  Got all 3 staves, go to Halas, realize the guards all want your head on a plate.  You can either stand behind the guy invis and be scared, OR you can get a chanter to project illusion Barbarian on you.  Yes, this is a high level skill. But, lets face it. If you REALLY look, you know a chanter who has it. With the PoK books, Halas is a 15 minute trip... dance for the chanter to make it worth his/her while. Turn in the note, and the Arantir (sp?) guy spawns.  IF your faction in Halas is Sooooooooo bad, illusion alone may not work. I don't have a solution for this. Get the illusion and con the locals, maybe you will survive.<br>
<br>
#5. DO NOT JUST GIVE HIM THE STAVES. Put all 3 staves in a trade window, get someone to invis you while the trade window is open. Con him, and be sure you are indiff.  If so, hit trade, get bag. Make sure you have a general inventory slot or a giant slot bag with a slot to recieve your reward.<br>
<br>
#6 Go to Sol Ro, Open trade window with bag, get invis, check to be sure you are indiff, hit trade. <br>
<br>
#7 /GU OMG I got Staff of the Four!!!  <br>
<br>
Of course, at this point you may well be in tears, so have the person helping you do the /gu for ya. It took me about 10 mins or so just to get mahari to link the silly thing for me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Feel bad for wizzies having the whole faction problem, stupid quest design, but such as life. Its not for us to question why, it is for us to find a way around it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Tarqal Evermore<br>
Mage of Xev, husband of Mahari the Epicced (and cute) Wizard<br>
